
** General Rule

  - Niall Litchfield wrote: Reduce response time this equates with
    reducing logical and phisical IO.

  - Sybrand Bakker wrote: The goal of your tuning should be to reduce
    the logical I/O, not to get the hit ratio up.

  - Do *not renice* anything.

** SGA Size

  - Hans Forbrich suggest do set the SGA size of 30 to 55 percent of
    physical memory to avoid swapping.


  - = sga_max_size: share_pool_size + large_pool_size + db_cache_size
    + sum(db_<n>k_cache_size) + log_buffer = 

  - = db_<n>k_cache_sizes = defaults to null.  This parameter are only
    used if different block sizes are used.  See too the 'Database
    Concepts' document.

** SQL_TRACE

  - All alter session statements needs the system privilege
    'alter session'.

  - http://www.petefinnigan.com/ramblings/how_to_set_trace.htm

** EVENTS 10046

  - alter session set events '10046 trace name context forever, level <n>'

  -  1 default
  -  4 bind variables
  -  8 waits
  - 12 bind variables and wait


  - dbms_system.set_ev (sid, serial#,10046,12)

